/**
 * @file Firestore Security Rules for Hesab Ketab Application
 * @description This ruleset enforces a strict user-ownership model for personal financial data and a shared access model for collaborative data, ensuring that users can only access data they own or have been explicitly granted access to.
 *
 * Data Structure:
 * All personal financial data is nested under /users/{userId}, ensuring that only the authenticated user with a matching UID can access it.
 * Shared financial data is stored under the /shared/data/{collection}/{documentId} path.  Each document under /shared/data has a `members` map which holds the UIDs of users who have access to that document.
 *
 * Key Security Decisions:
 * - Users can only manage data under their own /users/{userId} path.
 * - Users cannot list all users in the database.
 * - Shared collections enforce access control through a `members` map on each document.
 * - The rules do not validate the data schema beyond critical authorization fields, allowing for flexible data shapes during prototyping.
 *
 * Denormalization for Authorization:
 * - All documents in user-owned collections include a `userId` field to simplify authorization checks (e.g., `/users/{userId}/bankAccounts/{bankAccountId}`).
 * - All documents in shared collections include a `members` map to explicitly define user roles and permissions (e.g., `/shared/data/bankAccounts/{bankAccountId}`).
 */
rules_version = '2';
